FORMER Minister of Information and Culture, Prince Tony Momoh, is dead. Momoh, a veteran journalist, served as Nigerian minister during the military regime of General Ibrahim Babangida between 1986 and 1990. He died at the age of 81 on Monday. He was one of the founders of the ruling All Progressives Congress. Momoh was born on 27 April 1939 in Auchi, Edo State. Details laterâ€¦ 